summary: An Ordinance authorizing and directing the City Engineer to incur an indebtedness against the General Fund of The City of Seattle, in the sum of Four Hundred Sixteen and 94/100 Dollars ($416.94), for the purpose of competing the improvement of Twenty-first Avenue Southwest et al., by constructing wooden walks, as authorized by Ordinance No. 21541, creating Local Improvement District No. 2142.
